(126, 1, '2020-01-03 08:31:27', '2020-01-03 08:31:27', '<p><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\r\n<p>Welcome to the Paris Van Java International Seminar  on Health, Economics, Social Science and Humanities (PVJ-ISHESSH 2020). Hosted by Universitas Muhammadiyah Tasikmalaya. This year’s PVJ-ISHESSH will take place on 15 April  2020 in Bandung, Indonesia.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Organized by:</strong></p>\r\n<p><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-100\" src=\"http://pvj-is.umtas.ac.id/hessh/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/UMTAS-Logo-Bening-300x300.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"157\" height=\"157\" /></p>\r\n<p><strong>Co-host:</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong> </strong></p>\r\n<h3>CALL FOR ABSTRACT</h3>\r\n<p>Authors are requested to submit <strong>an abstract</strong> to the Organizing Committee before <strong>15 April 2020</strong>. The abstract must contain the following section: introduction, aim of the study, method, results, conclusion, and keywords. The abstract must have no longer than 200 words. <strong>[IMPORTANT]</strong> To submit an abstract, authors must create an account <strong>(</strong><a href=\"https://bis.ummgl.ac.id/ase/submission/\">click here</a><strong>)</strong>. Then they can go to “<a href=\"https://bis.ummgl.ac.id/ase/submission/\"><strong>Submit Your Paper</strong></a>” or “<a href=\"https://bis.ummgl.ac.id/hess/submission/\"><strong>Submission System</strong></a>” then “<a href=\"https://bis.ummgl.ac.id/ase/submission/\"><strong>Login</strong></a>” to submit the abstract. The submitted abstracts will be selected for presentation. The manuscripts (full papers) should be submitted only after the abstracts are accepted. The paper must be submitted <strong>before</strong>the conference day <strong>(15 April 2020)</strong>. <strong>All papers will be published in </strong><a href=\"https://www.scimagojr.com/journalsearch.php?q=130053&amp;tip=sid&amp;clean=0\">Proceeding</a><strong>s Indexed by Scopus/WoS. </strong>However, selected papers have the opportunity for publishing in Scopus Indexed Journals <strong>with additional charge</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>Therefore the author should follow the<strong> </strong><a href=\"https://bis.ummgl.ac.id/ase/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/WordGuidelines-18-37-31-235-1.zip\"><strong>article template.</strong></a> The papers should be written in English and must be between 4 to 6 pages.</p>\r\n<table width=\"100%\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>DOWNLOAD PAPER TAMPLATE</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<h3>BACKGROUND</h3>\r\n<p>Welcome to the 1st Paris Van Java International Seminar on Health, Economics, Social Science and Humanities. Hosted by Universitas Muhammadiyah Tasikmalaya (UMTAS). The 1st PVJ-ISHESSH brings up <strong>“Innovation for better life”</strong> as its theme. The main purposes of the conference are (1) to bring together the scientists, researchers and practitioners, students, and civil society organization representatives in the scientific forum; and (2) to share and to discuss theoretical and practical knowledge about innovation in health, economics, sosial science and humanities. In a more practical context, the conference is expected to become a platform of discussion among researchers, particularly the young ones, in the field of health, economics, sosial science and humanities. Therefore, the invited speakers in this conference are young researchers who have good reputation in the world.</p>\r\n<h2>SCOPE:</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Public Health</li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: 0px;\">Health Administration</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: 0px;\">Hospitality</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: 0px;\">Psychology</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: 0px;\">Communication</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: 0px;\">Economics</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: 0px;\">Education</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: 0px;\">Government Studies</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: 0px;\">International Relations</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: 0px;\">Law</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: 0px;\">Political Studies </span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: 0px;\">Art &amp; Linguistics</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: 0px;\">Religious Studies</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: 0px;\">Sociology</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: 0px;\"> and other related topics</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Keynote Speakers</strong></h3>\r\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-102\" src=\"http://pvj-is.umtas.ac.id/hessh/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Sayuti.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"172\" height=\"210\" /></p>\r\n<p><strong>Muhammad Sayuti, Ph.D.</strong></p>\r\n<p>(Majelisdiktilitbang PP Muhammadiyah)</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Prof. Sakinah Harith</strong></p>\r\n<p>(Universiti Sultan Zainal Abidin/UnisZa, Malaysia)</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Prof. Dr. Suswandari</strong></p>\r\n<p>(Universitas Muhammadiyah Prof.Dr.Hamka)</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Prof. Dr.Harun Joko Prayito , M.Hum.</p>\r\n<p>(Universitas Muhammadiyah Surakarta)</p>\r\n<p>Prof. Dr. Anna Permanasari, M.Si. </p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Venue and Activities</h3>\r\n<p><strong>ASTON Pasteur Hotel, Baandung</strong></p>\r\n<p>Jl. Dr. Djunjunan No.162, Sukagalih, Kec. Sukajadi, Kota Bandung, Jawa Barat 40162</p>\r\n<p><strong> </strong></p>\r\n<h3>Important Date</h3>\r\n<p>Abstract Submission Deadline :February 14, 2020</p>\r\n<p>Notification ff Abstract Acceptance: February 21, 2020</p>\r\n<p>Payment Deadline: March 5, 2020</p>\r\n<p>Full Paper Submission Deadline: April 14, 2020</p>\r\n<p>Conference Day: April 15, 2020</p>\r\n<p>Full Paper Revision Submis