xed by Scopus/WoS. </strong>However, selected papers have the opportunity for publishing in Scopus Indexed Journals <strong>with additional charge</strong>.\r\n\r\nTherefore the author should follow the<strong> </strong><strong>article template.</strong> The papers should be written in English and must be between 4 to 6 pages.\r\n<table width=\"100%\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>DOWNLOAD PAPER TAMPLATE</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<h3>BACKGROUND</h3>\r\nWelcome to the 1st Paris Van Java International Seminar on Health, Economics, Social Science and Humanities. Hosted by Universitas Muhammadiyah Tasikmalaya (UMTAS). The 1st PVJ-ISHESSH brings up <strong>“Innovation for better life”</strong> as its theme. The main purposes of the conference are (1) to bring together the scientists, researchers and practitioners, students, and civil society organization representatives in the scientific forum; and (2) to share and to discuss theoretical and practical knowledge about innovation in health, economics, sosial science and humanities. In a more practical context, the conference is expected to become a platform of discussion among researchers, particularly the young ones, in the field of health, economics, sosial science and humanities. Therefore, the invited speakers in this conference are young researchers who have good reputation in the world.\r\n<h2>SCOPE:</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Public Health</li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: 0px;\">Health Administration</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: 0px;\">Hospitality</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: 0px;\">Psychology</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: 0px;\">Communication</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: 0px;\">Economics</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: 0px;\">Education</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"font-s